The paper discusses the use of virtual borders in mobile robots and their interaction with humans, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of human-robot interaction methods, which is a subfield of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The proposed interaction method involves the use of cameras and laser pointers, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the integration of robots into intelligent environments, which involves multimedia (cs.MM).
